    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;On inter-router point-to-point links, it is useful, for security and other reasons, to use 127-bit IPv6 prefixes.  Such a practice parallels the use of 31-bit prefixes in IPv4.  This document specifies the motivation for, and usages of, 127-bit IPv6 prefix lengths on inter-router point-to-point links. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
